ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: How similar are you now to what you will be like 10 years from now?
Notes: 1 = Completely different; 2 = Somewhat different; 3 = A little different; 4 = Similar; 5 = Very similar; 6 = Exactly the same

ElementDescription: How similar are your beliefs now to what they will be like 10 years from now?
Notes: 1 = Completely different; 2 = Somewhat different; 3 = A little different; 4 = Similar; 5 = Very similar; 6 = Exactly the same

ElementDescription: How similar is your personality now to what it will be like 10 years from now?
Notes: 1 = Completely different; 2 = Somewhat different; 3 = A little different; 4 = Similar; 5 = Very similar; 6 = Exactly the same

ElementDescription: How similar are your values now to what they will be like 10 years from now?
Notes: 1 = Completely different; 2 = Somewhat different; 3 = A little different; 4 = Similar; 5 = Very similar; 6 = Exactly the same

Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Not very well; 3 = Somewhat; 4 = Pretty well; 5 = Very strongly; 6 = Perfectly

Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Not very well; 3 = Somewhat; 4 = Pretty well; 5 = Very strongly; 6 = Perfectly

Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Not very well; 3 = Somewhat; 4 = Pretty well; 5 = Very strongly; 6 = Perfectly

ElementDescription: Do you like what your actions will probably be like 10 years from now?
Notes: 1 = Not at all; 2 = Not very well; 3 = Somewhat; 4 = Pretty well; 5 = Very strongly; 6 = Perfectly

ElementDescription: Similarity to future self subscale
Vividness of future self subscale
Positive affect to future self subscale
Future Self-Continuity Questionnaire (FSCQ) score
How similar do you feel to a future self 15 years from now?
Notes: 1 = Not similar at all; 2 = Slightly similar; 3 = A little similar; 4 = Mildly similar; 5 = Somewhat similar; 6 = Moderately similar; 7 = Pretty much similar; 8 = Completely similar

ElementDescription: How connected do you feel to a future self 15 years from now?
Notes: 1= Not connected at all; 2 = Slightly connected; 3 = A little connected; 4 = Mildly connected; 5 = Somewhat connected; 6 = Moderately connected; 7 = Pretty much connected; 8 = Completely connected
